quran[37]{c,v,t}:
  19,22,So she bore him then withdrew with him to a distant place
  19,23,"And the pains of childbirth drove her to the trunk of a palm tree. She said, \"I wish I had died before this and had become forgotten (as something) to be forgotten"
  19,24,"Then she was called from beneath her, “Do not grieve, your Lord has made a rivulet beneath you"
  19,25,"and shake the trunk of the date palm towards you, making ripe dates to fall down to you"
  19,26,"Then eat and drink and cool (your) eye, and if you see any man then say: I have vowed a fast to the Beneficent, therefore I will not speak to any man today"
  19,27,"Then she came to her people carrying him (Jesus). They (her people) said, \"O mary !you have come with a strange thing"
  19,28,O sister of Aaron ! your father was not a bad man nor your mother was one who exceeded the limits
  19,29,"So she pointed towards him (Jesus, for the explanation). They said, \"How can we talk to one who is a child in the cradle?”"
  19,30,"He (Jesus) said, \"I am a servant of God, He has given me the book and made me a prophet"
  19,31,And He has made me blessed wherever I may be and has enjoined on me worship (salat) and (giving of) charity (zakat) as long as I live
  19,32,"And (He has made me) dutiful to my mother and has not made me compelling (rebellious), wretched"
  19,33,And peace be on me the day I was born and the day I die and the day I will be raised alive
  19,34,"Such (was) Jesus, the Son of Mary. (This is a) statement of the fact about which they doubt"
  19,35,"It is not befitting to God that He should take to Himself a son, glory be to Him, when He decrees an affair, He says to it only \"Be,\" so it is"
  19,36,"And God is certainly my Lord and your Lord so serve Him, this is the straight path"
  19,37,But the parties disagreed among themselves. So sorrowful will be the state of those who do not believe because of their being present on the great day
  19,38,"How clearly will they hear and how clearly will they see on the day they come to Us, but this day the unjust are in clear error"
  19,39,"And warn them of the day of regret when the affair will be decided, and (at present) they are in a state of heedlessness and (therefore) they do not believe"
  19,40,We will inherit the earth and whoever is on it and they will be returned to Us. (R)
  19,41,"And mention in the book (about) Abraham, he was certainly a truthful man, a prophet"
  19,42,"When he said to his father, \"O My father! why do you worship that which neither hears nor sees nor does it make you care-free from anything"
  19,43,"O my father! there has come to me of knowledge, (something) which has not come to you. So follow me I will guide you to the balanced path"
  19,44,"O my father! do not worship the devil, the devil is certainly disobedient to the Beneficent (God)"
  19,45,"O my father ! I fear that a punishment from the Beneficent (God) may afflict you, then you will become a friend of the devil"
  19,46,"He said, \"Do you forsake my gods O Abraham. If you do not desist I will definitely stone you, now go away from me for a long time"
  19,47,"He said, \"Peace be on you ! I will seek protective forgiveness of my Lord for you, He is certainly Gracious to me"
  19,48,"And I will withdraw from you and that which you pray to besides God, and I will pray to my Lord, may be that I will not be unsuccessful in my prayer to my Lord"
  19,49,"So when he withdrew from them and that which they worshipped besides God, We granted to him Isaac and Jacob and We made each one of them a prophet"
  19,50,And We granted to them from Our mercy and We assigned to them a high and true renown. (R)
  19,51,"And mention in the book (about) Moses, he was one who was purified and he was a messenger, a prophet"
  19,52,And We called him from the right (hand) side of the Mount Toor and drew him nearer for secret talk
  19,53,"And We granted to him from Our mercy, his brother Aaron, a prophet"
  19,54,"And mention in the book (about) Ishmael, he was truthful in his promise and he was a messenger, a prophet"
  19,55,And he used to enjoin on his people worship (salat) and charity (zakat) and he was one with whom his Lord was pleased
  19,56,"And mention in the book (about) Enoch, he was a truthful man, a prophet"
  19,57,and We raised him to a high place
  19,58,"Those are the persons on whom God bestowed (His) favour, from among the prophets from the descendants of Adam and from among those whom We carried with Noah (in the ship) and from among the descendants of Abraham and Israel and from among those whom We guided and chose, when the communications of the Beneficent (God) were read to them they fell down prostrating and weeping"